  "prompt": "Do we have Financial Management in IPCC group 1 in may 2017? Websites show change in syllabus.",
  "response": "Yes, there was a change in the syllabus for the IPCC (Intermediate (Integrated Professional Competence) Course) of ICAI (Institute of Chartered Accountants of India) effective from May 2017 onwards. Prior to this change, Financial Management was part of Paper 3, named \"Cost Accounting and Financial Management\" in IPCC Group 1.\n\nHowever, with the revised syllabus, Financial Management was shifted to the new Paper 8, named \"Financial Management & Economics for Finance\" in IPCC Group 2. Consequently, Group 1 no longer included Financial Management as part of its syllabus after the changes implemented in May 2017.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, it is advisable to refer to the official ICAI website or contact ICAI directly.",
